    "time": "2025.02.14",
    "abstract": "an angular analysis of $B^0 \\to K^{*0} e^+ e^-$ decays and a test of lepton flavour universality by comparing the obtained angular observables with those measured in $B^0 \\to K^{*0} \\mu^+ \\mu^-$ decays, using proton-proton collision data collected by the LHCb experiment at centre-of-mass energies of 7, 8 and 13TeV, corresponding to an integrated luminosity of 9 fb$^{-1}$, and performed in the region of the dilepton invariant mass squared of 1.1-6.0 GeV$^2/c^4$ as well as 1.1-7.0 GeV$^2/c^4$",
